{
  "stem": "19923.2",
  "chunk_idx": 12,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 9.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And when she came down, they looked at his passport, and they discovered that the visa had only one more day to go.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But they arranged for him to stay there, and that's how he was able to get out.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he-- he got his visa extended or whatever he was able to do.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And eventually, he joined the British Army during the war.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "He served in the Commandos, became honorably discharged, lived a long and fruitful life in London, has two children who are alive and well-- alive and well today, Marlene [?",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Nepler ?] and Richard Gordon, and they have children.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So my father, though, went to his village, and that's where he stayed.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He-- I heard later on he found out-- this-- the story will go on-- that we were able to get into Brussels, into Belgium.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And he made an attempt to try and join us and from [NON-ENGLISH], from [NON-ENGLISH], and he got as far as the border between Belgium and Germany.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And he couldn't go any further, and he was shipped back.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Now, after my father and uncle were deported, Joe tried to see-- now at 10 years old, he's the head of the family-- he's trying to see whether or not he could get us out into-- into Holland.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So he takes a train by himself to see if they could get in.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "He got out of Germany, but in Holland they turned him back.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He didn't have the proper paperwork.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "The Germans, at that time, were willing to let the-- the Jews out of Germany without difficulty.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 29,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It became a problem for them to come in to the neighboring countries.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 30,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So after they shipped him back the same day, my mother was able to contact some of her relatives.",
      "word_count": 19
    }
  ],
